  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:BreakdownElementDescription xmi:id="-vBhABYiRoFhhTQ4ToGtKHw" name="uam_review_existing,_26jYoKsbEeSFIOC-Wm7nrA" guid="-vBhABYiRoFhhTQ4ToGtKHw">
    <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The architectural review done in&amp;nbsp;this context involves ensuring that the architecture addresses the objectives of&#xD;
    the IT architecture project, and that it describes the existing system in enough detail to permit proceeding to the&#xD;
    next steps, as defined in the objectives of the IT architecture project.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Evaluation Criteria:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Existing architectures have been reviewed and summarized.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../UAM/workproducts/uam_arch_context-objectives_874E760A.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;_tjC3QMOdEdyILM4NThxMFg&quot;>Context and Objectives&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;has been defined and met.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Agreement on defined Architectural Decisions has been reached.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The required Simple Models of the existing system&amp;nbsp;have been defined and agreed.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Main Artifacts:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;strong>Simple Architecture Models&lt;/strong>&amp;nbsp;- completed;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;strong>Architecture Decisions&lt;/strong> - stable and agreed by all stakeholders;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;strong>Business Glossary&lt;/strong> -&amp;nbsp;refined.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>Typically a &quot;stakeholder review&quot; is done once this peer review has been completed. See: &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithType&quot;&#xD;
href=&quot;./../../UAM/deliveryprocesses/uam_architecture_review_524E0258.html&quot; guid=&quot;_aBL6oMhSEdyU89e0dKAsrw&quot;>Phase: Review the&#xD;
Architecture&lt;/a>. THis may be overridden by the fact that this is an existing architecture, which was defined for a&#xD;
specific purpose.</mainDescription>
    <usageGuidance>This review milestone is&amp;nbsp;a formal&amp;nbsp;&lt;em>peer review&lt;/em> where&amp;nbsp;the IT architecture is reviewed by IT experts,&#xD;
other participants, and peers to ensure that it is complete, consistent, and meets objectives.&amp;nbsp;</usageGuidance>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:BreakdownElementDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:ActivityDescription xmi:id="-b2skqzoJM6nqBlbJcHX7ig" name="ea_logical_arch_review,_Y4WJgEPyEeShYIpiBstbOQ" guid="-b2skqzoJM6nqBlbJcHX7ig">
    <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    This activity is focused on organizing and doing&amp;nbsp;a stakeholder review of&amp;nbsp;the Logical Perspective of the&#xD;
    system. Appropriate materials are gathered, venues booked and participants informed.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The review focuses on the generated models, ensuring that they are complete and consistent, which is normally part of a&#xD;
    peer review, but is also done as the first step of this review.&amp;nbsp;A review of&amp;nbsp;the content of the architecture&#xD;
    in terms of how accurately it captures the business and the supporting solution is then done, which focuses on aspects&#xD;
    of interest to the main stakeholders. These stakeholders have intimate knowledge of the area of the business in&#xD;
    question, and have a vested interest in the results of the IT architecture project.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Actions are documented, assigned&amp;nbsp;and tracked in a Review Record.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
    <usageGuidance>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Mandatory for&amp;nbsp;all architecture efforts since it in essence is the final approval for the IT architecture. It also&#xD;
    provides valuable feedback to architects from peers and stakeholders.&#xD;
&lt;/p></usageGuidance>
    <purpose>&lt;a id=&quot;XE_Delivery__Review_Logical&quot; name=&quot;XE_Delivery__Review_Logical&quot;>&lt;/a> &#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The purpose is to ensure that there is cohesion and agreement in the models, from the architecture perspective and get&#xD;
    agreement from stakeholders. Also to generally improve the quality of the architecture and the architects through the&#xD;
    provision of feedback.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Once an IT architecture perspective is completed, two types of reviews are undertaken:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        A&amp;nbsp;&lt;em>peer review&lt;/em> of the results is done prior to moving on to next steps, which focuses on the&#xD;
        consistency, completeness and cohesiveness of the architecture. This review is done at the end of the development&#xD;
        of the perspective, for example: &lt;a class=&quot;elementLinkWithType&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../UAM/deliveryprocesses/uam_business_milestone_78D9E3AB.html&quot; guid=&quot;_Uw7RMN5nEdyg17nU3bVmlA&quot;>Milestone:&#xD;
        Business Perspective Milestone&lt;/a>.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        A second phase, the &lt;em>stakeholder review&lt;/em> described here, focuses on the content of the architecture in terms&#xD;
        of how accurately it captures the business, which normally involves a number of stakeholders that have intimate&#xD;
        knowledge of the area of the business in question, and at the correct level, namely Business, Logical&amp;nbsp;or&#xD;
        Technical.&amp;nbsp;This is the final &quot;approval&quot; step for the IT architecture perspective.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    These reviews document deficiencies, errors and omissions in a &quot;Review Record&quot;, which the architect then actions (i.e.,&#xD;
    models etc. are updated or changed as needed). The recommended next steps are also identified for later approval and&#xD;
    action.&#xD;
&lt;/p></purpose>
