        Business goals and strategies have been&amp;nbsp;reviewed and summarized, and the defined architecture supports them.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../UAM/workproducts/uam_arch_context-objectives_874E760A.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;_tjC3QMOdEdyILM4NThxMFg&quot;>Context and Objectives&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;has been reviewed.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The &lt;em>to-be&lt;/em> business has been modeled.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Agreement on defined Architectural Decisions has been reached.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The&amp;nbsp;&lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../UAM/workproducts/uam_perspective_logical_40FE04D0.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;_Py-hINT-EdyakOJbsHza1A&quot;>Logical Perspective&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;has been defined and agreed and the&amp;nbsp;architect peer&#xD;
        review completed.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Major risks / issues have been addressed and the stakeholders agreed with the resolutions.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;h5>&#xD;
    Main Artifacts:&#xD;
&lt;/h5>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;strong>Logical Perspective&lt;/strong> - completed;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;strong>Architecture Decisions&lt;/strong> - stable and agreed by all stakeholders;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;strong>Architecture Glossary&lt;/strong> -&amp;nbsp;defined and refined;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;strong>Review Record&lt;/strong> - agreed and documented.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></refinedDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-q5LBrG881ZclEYN-gVu21g" name="ea_review_tech_models,_5xsTMEP0EeShYIpiBstbOQ" guid="-q5LBrG881ZclEYN-gVu21g">
    <usageGuidance>The review of the Technical Perspective is&amp;nbsp;very much at the technical level. Most stakeholders at this level are&#xD;
technical, but business domain experts are also involved and their voice needs to be heard.&amp;nbsp;Take the time to ensure&#xD;
that all stakeholders have their say and that agreement is reached on any issues that arise. It is imperative that domain&#xD;
and business process experts for the business in question provide feedback and that technical reviewers understand the&#xD;
concerns of the business. Conflicts may arise, which need to be addressed prior to the completion of this review, if&#xD;
possible.</usageGuidance>
    <refinedDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The architectural review involves ensuring that the architecture addresses the business need and fits in with the&#xD;
    enterprise direction in the long-term. Scenarios may be used to test the architecture. If there is a problem in the&#xD;
    direction taken by the architecture (which needs to be documented and justified)&amp;nbsp;in terms of the enterprise&#xD;
    long-term objectives or standards then management will review and bless this deviation in direction. This Technical&#xD;
    level review is where the technical experts must be heard and their issues addressed, since this level defines the&#xD;
    technologies to be used.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h5>&#xD;
    Evaluation Criteria:&#xD;
&lt;/h5>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Business goals and strategies have been&amp;nbsp;reviewed and summarized, and the defined architecture supports them.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../UAM/workproducts/uam_arch_context-objectives_874E760A.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;_tjC3QMOdEdyILM4NThxMFg&quot;>Context and Objectives&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;has been reviewed.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The &lt;em>to-be&lt;/em> business has been modeled.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Agreement on defined Architectural Decisions has been reached.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The&amp;nbsp;&lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot; href=&quot;./../../UAM/workproducts/uam_perspective_technical_BED9D321.html&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;_Tms8ENWbEdyLINQdtlJihw&quot;>Technical Perspective&lt;/a>&lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../UAM/workproducts/uam_perspective_logical_40FE04D0.html&quot; guid=&quot;_Py-hINT-EdyakOJbsHza1A&quot;>Logical&#xD;
        Perspective&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;has been defined and agreed and the&amp;nbsp;architect peer review completed.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Major risks / issues have been addressed and the stakeholders agreed with the resolutions.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;h5>&#xD;
    Main Artifacts:&#xD;
&lt;/h5>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;strong>Technical Perspective&lt;/strong> - completed;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;strong>Architecture Decisions&lt;/strong> - stable and agreed by all stakeholders;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;strong>Architecture Glossary&lt;/strong> -&amp;nbsp;defined and refined;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;strong>Review Record&lt;/strong> - agreed and documented.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></refinedDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-94Anv2hyhJE2HZCpNuigDA" name="ea_scan_ads_logical,_y-SjQN8NEdynr9jlfK-aMA" guid="-94Anv2hyhJE2HZCpNuigDA">
    <usageGuidance>Scanning Architectural Decisions helps in setting the stage and context for the business architecture effort to come. This&#xD;
effort will either use these decisions or modify them as required. ADs are scanned, and an AD Summary produced, to ensure&#xD;
that this is available for stakeholders during the development of the perspective.</usageGuidance>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-72oTz9T0YLEZDQr2V1eRwg" name="ea_scan_ads_tech,_n29zEd8ZEdynr9jlfK-aMA" guid="-72oTz9T0YLEZDQr2V1eRwg">
    <usageGuidance>Scanning Architectural Decisions helps in setting the stage and context for the business architecture effort to come. This&#xD;
effort will either use these decisions or modify them as required. ADs are scanned, and an AD Summary produced, to ensure&#xD;
that this is available for stakeholders during the development of the perspective.</usageGuidance>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-l4K5xKPotW3TQ9zzER9o9A" name="ea_define_ad_business,_x99y4N8GEdynr9jlfK-aMA" guid="-l4K5xKPotW3TQ9zzER9o9A">
    <usageGuidance>Architectural Decisions may be defined at any time during the development of the Business Perspective. There are typically&#xD;
very few ADs defined at the Business level, and those that are defined relate to business processes and their relationships&#xD;
and&amp;nbsp;structure.</usageGuidance>
    <refinedDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The purpose of this activity is to create an Architecture Decision (AD), specifically to:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Define the context of the problem, issue or decision;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Define the constraints, imposed by existing architecture, enterprise standards or others;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Define the rationale for the decision, through a well researched summary of the facts;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Extract the implications of the AD, on current systems, future systems, support aspects and other aspects;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Define the specifics of the decision.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    This activity results in the production of an AD. The diagram illustrates the main inputs and outputs of this activity&#xD;
    as hinted at above. A problem context helps to define the scope of the AD, and the constraints (imposed by technology,&#xD;
    the current situation, etc.) along with the rational (that is very much local to the business and the context) help in&#xD;
    arriving at and defining the decision. Implications of this decision, on the business and the current situation, are&#xD;
    also extracted and defined.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;blockquote style=&quot;MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        &lt;img alt=&quot;AD Rationale&quot; src=&quot;./../../UAM/tasks/./resources/AD_rationale.png&quot; />&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;/blockquote>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    This is explained in more detail in the descriptions of the steps involved.&#xD;
&lt;/p></refinedDescription>
  </org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription>
  <org.eclipse.epf.uma:DescriptorDescription xmi:id="-uBQFFzA83V93Lm4_cEpiig" name="ea_define_ad_logical,_UvWqAN8OEdynr9jlfK-aMA" guid="-uBQFFzA83V93Lm4_cEpiig">
